PARIS - Lisbon's famed Stadium of Light and Istanbul's Ataturk Olympic stadium are the two grounds in the running to host the 2019/2020 Champions League final, European governing body UEFA said Friday. A decision will be made in June 2018. This season's Champions League final will take place in Kiev with the 2018/2019 finale slated for the Wanda Metropolitano, the new home of Atletico Madrid. For the 2019/2020 Europa League final, the host will be either Gdansk in Poland or Porto's Dragao arena in Portugal. The 2020 women's Champions League final will be held in either Vienna, Liege or Moscow. AFP